        <p>
          Enter Kiran.  From a town called Edison in New Jersey, she eats gobi  and dances a lot.  She also does a little computer science.  At home, there was one dish she could not stay away from: Gobi Manchurian.  Her parents began to wonder why she asked for it so much, and she even choreographed a Bollywood dance for it.  She worked so hard, just doing a little front end work (choosing all the colors) to bring you this website, so the other people in this world could also see why she loves Gobi so much.  JK Kiran did most of the front end work. Also she chose her prom dress while thinking about hex color codes.  

        </p>
