        <p>  
         Kim, who longboarded to MIT all the way from the streets of LA, thought she had everything that would make her life content.  She decided to go on an adventure to India last summer. One day, Kim woke up, brushed her teeth, went to her internship (in Bangalore), but little did she know her life would change.  When she went out to dinner that day, she ordered Gobi Manchurian.  Once Gobi became a part of her life, nothing was the same.  She began to believe in the power that is Gobi.  Back here at MIT, as she hopes to share this discovery she made in India, she brings you this website.
